<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 20 at 5:42PM EST  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A LIGHT ACCUMULATION OF SNOW THROUGH THIS EVENING...
Temperatures will drop into the upper 20s to lower 30s this
evening. A period of light snow early this evening should taper
off toward midnight. Most locations will pick up less than an
inch, but could see around an inch toward Staunton River State
Park to east of Yanceyville.
With temperatures falling, be alert to slippery roads if traveling
through this evening.</description>
